CENTRAL PET UPDATE


WINGS & CLIPSTRIPS ON ENDCAPS =E2=80=94 SCOPE =
CLARIFIED

Jen and Ramon confirmed how the new endcap program applies =
across Pet Center ends and wings.

QUICK HIT LIST

=E2=80=A2 Service ALL =
endcaps and wings in the Pet Center / pet aisles =E2=80=94 count varies by =
store =E2=80=A2 SKIP WOW ends and Purina ends with the long fronts / TV =
screens =E2=80=A2 Endcap clipstrips (flat, one-sided) are separate from the=
 permanent double-sided wing fixture program =E2=80=A2 Prioritize the =
Lennox/Lifebound wing =E2=80=94 merchandise landed in the warehouse early =
=E2=80=A2 Expect longer store visits while this program ramps up

Hi team,

Following up on the questions about the new Wings & Clipstrips on Endcaps =
program =E2=80=94 Jen Ludolf and Ramon Bracamonte gave us the clarification=
 we needed. Here is what your reps need to know before their next visits.

Scope per store:

 * Every store has a different number of endcaps and =
wings in the Pet Center =E2=80=94 some have 6 pet ends, others only 1 or 2.=
 There is no fixed count.
 * Service all endcaps and wings the store has in=
 the pet center / pet aisles.
 * Do NOT service the WOW ends or Purina ends=
 with the longer fronts and TV screens.

Two different programs =E2=80=94 =
don't mix them up:

 * Endcap clipstrips =E2=80=94 lay flat, one-sided, sit=
 on the endcap.
 * Permanent wing fixtures =E2=80=94 double-sided, attached=
, have their own designated items and POG.

Lennox / Lifebound wing: =
Merchandise arrived at the warehouse earlier than expected. Please treat =
this as a priority wing when ordering for your stores.

Time expectations: Ramon confirmed this program will take longer per store =
visit than a normal service. Plan routes accordingly and flag any stores =
where the added workload is a real problem.

If your reps still have =
questions on which fixture is which, ping me and I'll walk it through.

Thanks,
Tyson

Action
Service every Pet Center endcap and wing your store =
has =E2=80=94 except WOW ends and Purina ends with the TV screens.

Product / display reference
Traditional endcap example from Central Pet's =
program documentation
